**How to Do a Trade Forecast the Right Way**

1. **Check the Year-on-Year Growth**  
   First, look at the percentage change from last June to this June, and from last July to this July.  
   This shows how much better (or worse) things got under the new management. It tells you their early impact.

2. **Use This Growth to Predict the Future**  
   Start with real trade numbers from **August 2025 to May 2026**.  
   Then, apply the **same % growth** you saw in June and July to each of those months to estimate **August 2026 to May 2027**.  
   This gives you a full-year forecast.

3. **Adjust for Diminishing Returns**  
   After this, don’t expect growth to keep going up by the same % every year.  
   Over time, the new management’s effect will fade.  
   So for each month after May 2027, you should still see higher numbers than the same month the year before—but the % increase should be smaller.
